board.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jharycleric>Jharycleric</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 422<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/6/02 2:44:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1941.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Work with the Roleplay</span><hr size=1> This is for all the people who roleplay, those who are heavy into it, and those who just nibble around the edges. Please do not dismiss anothers character merely based on your like/dislike of their origin story. For all the complaining about lack of roleplayers, if someone is roleplaying, even if you think the concept is whack, at least try and roleplay WITH them. <br>
<br>
Three times in the last week I have seen people who roleplay outright dismiss another player because of their Drizzit/High Elf gone bad/flip flop of roles style of character origin. Look, you might not like the origin, but the other person was ROLEPLAYING and my god, according to just about everybody, that's getting more and more difficult to find. I'm not asking you to group with them. I'm not saying they are great folk, invite 'em to all your guild parties, they do a great comedy routine. I'm saying, cripes, interact with them, try roleplaying, maybe they will become a perfect foil for you. <br>
My best times roleplaying have been with the Ven Sho, who if they can accept my guild as Iksar Exiles/Outcasts (with a goblin attached) then just about anything can happen. Please though, just don't outright give 'em the back of your roleplaying hand cause you don't like the origin story. On this server, it's like cutting your own throat.<br>
<br>
Jhary<br>
Iksar Cleric<br>
Prophetic Alliance<br>
Pimping Neutrality 24/7  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thessalyathelas>ThessalyAthelas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 306<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/6/02 4:18:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1941.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Work with the Roleplay</span><hr size=1> <br>
Word.<br>
<br>
Even though  it may seem cliche', there's something compelling about the fallen &quot;good&quot;, or the &quot;evil&quot; with a heart of gold. I know it seems like some people are just trying to work around guild alignment issues on this specific server, but that doesn't mean every backstory like that is invalid. <br>
<br>
I'm not the world's greatest RPer, but my first character on Innoruuk (before FV ever existed) was a High Elf   cleric. For whatever reason, I pictured her at odds with the church of Felwithe, being unpious or pissing off the church fathers by being too mouthy. I wrote up her backstory that way in my very first guild.  There's a reason we're drawn to these anti-stereotypes; conflict and contradiction makes things more interesting.<br>
<br>
 <p>Gwynne Athelas<br>
High Priestess of Tunare<br>
