<br>
Caillou dismisses the idea a Teir'dal can be good.  SHE doesn't believe it is possibly and will tell one to his/her face that it isn't and then give them the back story of the creation of the Tier'dal, the backstory she grew up learning, the backstory some of those she has met in her life still bear the scars of.  <br>
<br>
So.... am I dismissing their roleplay because Caillou does not accept them?<br>
<br>
Or... in order to &quot;work&quot; with an evil who is &quot;good&quot;, is Caillou suppose to accept their story and rejoice that they have found the light and are now on the right side and give them aide and assistance and invite them to tea?<br>
<br>
The former IS interacting with them.  It is even interacting with their storyline while also maintaining Caillou's.  The later.. I'm sorry, but if that is what I am -required- to do to be considered interacting with them... well... I might as well delete all the EQ software on my computers, close my accounts and walk away.  <br>
<br>
In, my opinon, Caillou's storyline, her RP, is -just- as important as anyone else's who RPs here.  But that seems to be the thing in contention... once again.<br>
<br>
Oh... and I am using Caillou just as an example.  This could be said of -any- RPer here.  Is the RP of one superceeded by the RP of another?<br>
